Class DisplayEvent

All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class DisplayEvent
extends EventObject

This event is sent to a DisplayListener from a DisplayManager's map drawing thread when it wants to signal one of the following events:

  • the drawing thread starts drawing on a particular DisplayArea
  • the drawing thread finishes drawing on a DisplayArea
  • the Display's extent has changed
You can cancel rendering threads, by invoking the Map's cancel() method

See Also:
DisplayListener, Map.cancel(), Serialized Form
